sec.p:
During the observation sessions, other unexpected alarm signals were observed; they were not included in the statistical analysis, but were very useful to better understand the animal behavior, so we decided to include them in this subsection. Such signals were performed by one animal in response to a higher disturbance and were probably aimed at alerting the whole group to the danger. The signals that we could observe were as follows:
Urination before flight (Figure 5a);
The stamping of the hoof on the ground (Figure 5b);
Defecation during flight (Figure 5c).
